"{\"uid\": \"dailypost.ng-2024-07-20-paris-2024-olympic-all-sports-event-team-nigeria-will-compete-in-full-list\", \"text\": \"Published  on  By  The 2024 Olympic Games in Paris, France, is just five days to go.  Nigeria is scheduled to compete at the 2024 Summer Olympics in Paris from 26 July to 11 August 2024.  A total of 88 athletes will represent the nation in different sports.  DAILY POST reports the sports event Team Nigeria will compete in.  Here is the list of all the sports event Team Nigeria will compete in:  AthleticsBadmintonBasketballBoxingCanoeingCyclingFootballTable TennisTaekwondoWeightliftingWrestling  Meanwhile, the Minister of Sports Development, Senator John Owan Enoh, had already stated that his aspiration is for Team Nigeria to surpass its best Olympic outing achieved at the 1996 Olympic Games in Atlanta, USA.  Enoh had called for Nigerians to throw their weight behind the nation throughout the Games.  \\\"Our athletes are putting in tremendous effort and dedication in their preparations,\\\" said Enoh in a statement by Diana-Mary Nsan,S.A. Media to the Honourable Minister of Sports Development.  \\\"We are confident that with the support of every Nigerian, our team will excel and make the nation proud.\\\"  Nigeria's contingent encompasses talented and world-class athletes such as Oluwatobiloba Amusan, Ese Brume, Blessing Oborodudu, the two Favours (Ashe and Ofili), Odunayo Adekouroye, Chukwuebuka Enekwechi, Aruna Quadri, among other names too numerous to mention.  Transfer: Chelsea, Napoli in talks over Osimhen's replacement, Lukaku  Highest-ranked footballers in list of top 100 athletes revealed  Paris 2024 Olympic: Nigeria's D'Tigress makes history after winning first game  Paris 2024 Olympic: Nigeria coach, Waldrum releases Super Falcons' starting XI against Spain  Paris 2024 Olympic: Huge blow as ITA suspend Nigerian boxer  Paris 2024 Olympic: Waldrum makes two demands from Super Falcons  Copyright \\u00a9Daily Post Media Ltd\"}"